Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
cloneMSVGate(25.10)                                        cloneMSVGate(25.10)

Name
       cloneMSVGate  -  Ensures that the cloned isolation or level shifter can
       drive a group of the receivers and be placed close to this group of re-
       ceivers

Syntax
       cloneMSVGate

       [-help]

       [-iso]

       [-shifter]

       [-instances <inst1 inst2 ....>]

       [-maxFanout <integer>]

       [-maxTran <num>]

       [-maxCap <num>]

       [-honorPrePlaced]

       [-honorDontTouch]

       Ensures that the cloned isolation or level shifter can drive a group of
       the receivers and be placed close to this group of receivers. By  doing
       this, the timing QoR can be improved.

       Note:  The command will not automatically update your CPF/IEEE1801 file
       to match the new netlist. It is advised  that  you  run  Conformal  Low
       Power  to  check  for  any issues. When the enable signal for isolation
       cells is cloned (creating new ports on the boundary of  the  power  do-
       main),  the  users  may  need to update create_isolation_rule in CPF or
       set_isolation in IEEE1801 by defining  the  isolation  control  differ-
       ently.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each cloneMSVGate parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man cloneMSVGate

       -honorDontTouch
              Does not clone don't touch instances or cells.

              The default is to clone don't touch instances.

       -honorPrePlaced
              Does not clone pre-placed (fixed) instances.

              The default is to clone fixed instances

       -instances <inst1 inst2 ...>
              Clones specified instances.

       -iso   Clones isolation cells.

       -maxFanout <integer>
              Specifies the maximum fanout count.

       -maxCap <num>
              An  optional  check  to clone instances with maximum capacitance
              violation.

              The default is not to use -maxCap violation.

       -maxTran <num>
              Cloning will be only on instances with maximum transition

              time violation.

              The default is 2ns.

       -shifter
              Clones level shifters.

Related Information
       Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

